\(\renewcommand{\hat}[1]{\widehat{#1}}\)

38_semi-log_get_log


  1. Question

    An exponential growth curve, \(y=B^x\) with base \(B>1\), is graphed below using a semi-log plot.


    Estimate \(\log_B(4)\).


    Solution

    Logarithms are inverses of exponential functions. So, if \(f(x)=B^x\) then \(f^{-1}(x)=\log_B(x)\). In this case, that means we know the \(y\) coordinate is 4, and we are looking for the \(x\) coordinate.

    It might help to see more labels on a small section of the \(y\) (logarithmic) axis.


    With that in mind, you just need to locate the correct spot on the graph.


    So, \[\log_B(4)~=~1.4\]
